{# 
    Command (<command>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines a command button that a user can invoke. Note that the <command>
        element is not widely supported in browsers.

    Variables:
    - `command_type`: The type of the command. Can be "command", "checkbox",
      or "radio". Defaults to "command".
    - `command_label`: The label of the command. Defaults to "Command".
    - `command_icon`: The URL of the icon for the command. Defaults to "icon.png".
    - `command_disabled`: Boolean to specify if the command should be disabled.
      Defaults to false.
    - `command_checked`: Boolean to specify if the command should be checked
      (for "checkbox" or "radio" types). Defaults to false.

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.
    - The <command> element is not widely supported and may not work in all browsers.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/command
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_command.asp

#}

<command 
    type="{{ command_type | default('command') | e }}" 
    label="{{ command_label | default('Command') | e }}" 
    icon="{{ command_icon | default('icon.png') | e }}" 
    {% if command_disabled | default(false) %}disabled{% endif %} 
    {% if command_type == 'checkbox' or command_type == 'radio' %}{% if command_checked | default(false) %}checked{% endif %}{% endif %}
>
